516		// the tunnel's stable Source (its derived-throughput state survives), and on a refuse
517		// (e.g. a newly non-loopback address) leaves the previous endpoint running and fails
518		// the reload — the running tunnel is never disturbed. Applied BEFORE the path diff so
519		// a metrics-refuse aborts before any membership change.
